      "writtenOn": "2018-07-18T22:03:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the general pattern for conditional variable waiting is a loop. Spurious wakeup may cause the test to fail otherwise\nuse the code like this:\n\nauto waitUntil \u003d time() + maxTimeout;\nAutoLock lock(mLock);\nwhile (!mHangDetected \u0026\u0026 cv.timedWait(mLock, waitUntil)) {\n    ;\n}\nEXPECT_TRUE(mHangDetected);\n\n1. calculate the point in time to wait until once, as the loop could use it many times\n2. lock the mutex to protect |mHangDetected| accesses\n3. check the bool variable first, as the parallel thread could\u0027ve already set it\n4. wait in a loop to neutralize potential spurious wakeups\n5. bail out on timeout (timedWait() \u003d\u003d false)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 54,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 54,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "77b7e64303951e58f6323c8d9f53eae012d55447",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
